,Recommended,214510,17360450,"Posted: 2 August, 2015",all,[slckr]robilar5500,"This was a pretty stellar game. I have played this off and on over the last couple years, lol....but that is no indictment on the game. Actually, my interest in both the topic and the LEGO aspect kept bringing me back, even though my gamer ADD often took hold. The humor added to a mostly dark adventure was perfect, and as somebody who knows the LOTR inside and out, I really appreciated all the subtle jokes and such. Often, they really said what a lot of fans were thinking. The gameplay itself is fairly standard LEGO game fare. Engaging and simple enough that anybody can pick up this game and play it through to its conclusion. I also like how they broke the game up into three books with credits at the end of each. That was appropriate IMO.The extras such as free roam and so on all are also what you would expect and could literally add countless hours to your game.My only complaint is that a played a couple chapters offline, and the game never synced those trophies afterwards, so it is kind of odd seeing my completion without some of the end of chapter achievements (like the Weathertop one for example).All in all, I would consider this a must own for LOTR and/or LEGO game fans. Very well done. Let's see, 16 rings of power out of 19 possible with one ring to rule them all."
,Recommended,214510,10891132,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,Yureina,"I'm very mixed on this one. On the one hand, its a charming and often funny adventure where you re-enact LOTR... with legos! I'd never played one of these lego games before, so I didn't know what to expect. What I found was a fun game with plenty of content taking a serious storyline and making it goofy as well....And yet this game frustrated me. Alot. For one, it's a terrible console port. There's no mouse support, so you have to do everything with the keyboard. I did manage to get through this, but it makes playing a little awkward. Worse for me is the platforming parts, where you have to jump around to reach hidden areas or to progress further in the levels. Trouble is the camera can be annoying with this, and it is far too easy to fall off ledges or into water, and then have to try again and again. I got seriously frustrated at a few parts, though ultimately I made it through. I'd call the platforming the worst part of this game.So it's a fun game with some frustrating elements. This is one of those cases where a ""maybe"" recommendation would be ideal, but ultimately I'll lean towards ""yes"" on this one because the good bits outweigh the frustrating bits. Have fun! :)"
