,Recommended,214510,8495516,"Posted: 1 January, 2014",all,Omelette du Fromage,"Take the characters, plot, world building and lore of The Lord of The Rings, add goofy humor and collect a ton platforming game play and you have this awesome game.This game really surprised me. The voice over and soundtrack are the same used in the movie trilogy. The're impeccable. The graphics are really nice. The characters models are, well legos. They are nice and all, but what robs the spotlight are the environments and the various middle-earth places and structures they created. Everything is very well done and you can recognize all of the places show in the movies.The game if filled with eater eggs. The majority of them form the movies, but some from the books too. This combined with the goofy humor really adds to the experience.Game play wise, the game is a collect a ton platformer that made me remember the good days of N64 and PS1 (Banjo-Kazooie , Crash, Donkey Kong, Spyro) with some basic rack and slash and puzzling. It's fun, but it hardly presents any challenge.My only criticism about the game are some 2 or 3 buggy platforming sections that were really annoying. In the end, it's a really nice game, and a great experience for Tolkien fans."
