,Recommended,214510,33882837,Posted: 29 July,all,agentcarr16,"It has been a long time since I first played LEGO Star Wars. My friends and I loved that game, and I have great memories. So when LEGO LOTR was on sale, I decided to pick it up for the nostalgia.PROS:- Classic LEGO gaming. Whacking foes, building structures, funny cutscenes, everything. Loved it.- Great level design. I never felt like I was playing reskinned levels. I've noticed that in a few games I played recently, but not in this one. Every level is different.- Every character can do almost everything!!! LEGO Star Wars needed certain characters for certain actions. LEGO LOTR allows any character to complete *almost* any action, using items.CONS:- Not as funny... LEGO Star Wars was laugh-out-loud hilarious. LEGO LOTR tries, but it just isn't as funny. There were only two or three cutscenes that I really laughed at.- Occasionally requires button-mashing. There were a couple of times where the game literally tells you to button mash. For minutes on end. Boring.- Too easy. LEGO Star Wars had a decent difficult curve, running around completing objectives. LEGO LOTR feeds everything to you.- Too many semi-cutscenes. Parts of the game where they show you what's coming up, but it isn't a full cutscene. They drove me crazy, since they're unskippable.- Custom characters need to have a cape? What's up with that??CONCLUSION:Felt really good to play a LEGO game again. Not quite as good as LEGO Star Wars, but still very well done. Some of the new abilities are great, and I really like being able play through a level with a single character, using only items to get through.FINAL RATING: 5/7"
