,Recommended,214510,31294529,Posted: 22 April,all,Globster.CZ,"This game is chill af. The puzzles are pleasurable and do not feel dumbed-down for kids because some of them can be quite tricky, especially in Free Play where you will have to utilise abilities of all characters in solving intriguing puzzles. I found jumping puzzles the most challenging. The camera in this game is quite clunky plus the horrible character changing mechanism making the game a bit frustrating at some points. The camera can be panned but I found the lack of mouse support a bit annoying. The cutscenes now have voiceovers taken directly from the films, which may seem strange at first, given that previous LEGO games were silent, but it makes the scenes more memorable. The slapstick humour is of very high quality, as is usual in Traveller's Tales' games. Even the scenes from the films that always made me cry obviously made me laugh. Howard Shore's soundtrack is very well edited into this game and is playing non-stop in the background making everything more epic/enjoyable. I only didn't like that they changed the iconic music playing during the ride of the Rohirrim, the last march of the Ents and the Gandalf's Eagles rescue at the end of all things. (would cry again)8/10"
