,Recommended,214510,31571666,Posted: 5 May,all,Blandy,"Having played both Lego Star Wars I + II and Marvel Heroes going into this, I knew what to expect gameplay wise but was a bit skeptical if the serious nature of the Lord of the RIngs films could be adapted into a Lego game and I have to say I got another solid experience. The storyline is condensed somewhat hitting all the major plotpoints so might not make a whole lot of narrative sense if you haven't seen the movies.If you've never played a Lego game before firstly I would recommend a controller, as they've predominantly been designed with consoles in mind. The main campaign will probably only take you around 9-12 hours but there is a good 18-20 hours of side content within the big open world hub map of Middle Earth if you enjoy the whole collect-a-thon type of gameplay.Be wary though that if you plan to play this game with friends (as Lego games are designed to be played) that there's only local co-op. Although unlike the previous titles I predominantly played this game almost completely in single-player and it was still super fun."
76561198027999803,Recommended,214510,31329005,Posted: 23 April,all,Scarface,"Wonderful game with both open word and instanced missions. Features many unique characters with different skills, cosmetic and ability items, some unique animations for some chars and many references. Many collectibles and some game changing optional features as reward for some quests. Very fun to play.The downside is the physics engine which have some collision issues, especially at higher resolution settings. This may cause some minor glitches like stuck character, weird movement behaviour on some terrains.""It won't be that easy!"" achievement may be impossible to get at higher resolutions and a few end-mission minikits where you have to smash objets while running and only controlling your side movement can be harder than usual to get at higher resolutions.None of these are gamebreaking though. The bad controls/camera sinergy is another annoying downside. Both issues combined can make plataform jumping a nightmare.TL;DR:This could be a 8.5/10 recomended at full price game, but because of collision issues and bad controls;camera interaction, it is actually a 6.5/10 recommended on a large discount."
