76561197983155187,Recommended,214510,9788030,"Posted: 11 April, 2014",all,MonkeyspankO,"9/10 Awesome game!  Well crafted cartoon style graphics consistant with the Lego theme. Lego parts feel like they have real weight/function in the world.  Challenging and rarely frustrating missions. Few if any bugs I can think of; one minor case of temperary clipping.  The dialogue is spoken, so no-Lego babble, can be a pro or con depending on your likes. Tons of extra content to un-lock!First, I'm a LOTR and Lego fan, so I am biased.  Even so, I would recommend this game to anyone who likes games with a good sense of humor.Some of the earlier Lego games may have turned off ""serious"" gamers, but imo they are definately getting better. I haven't played them all, but this one was a very positive surprise.First, they put all the main LOTR movies in one game, so there is very little padding (un-like say in the Star Wars Lego games).  The main story goes through most of the major plots points in well designed, fun and most importanly non-frustrating levels/missions. Once you leave the Shire the world opens up, offering plenty of exploring. Its not a GTA game of course, but the world is intuitive and fun.Once you finish the main stories, you can unlock free-play. I found this easily added a good chunk of play hours.  There are entire mini-levels that you would miss completely if you had not unlocked the required mini-figs to access them!Final word, get a decent gamepad, leave your cynicism at the door and have fun."
