,Not Recommended,214510,14340816,"Posted: 5 February, 2015",all,Manbeast,"I couldn't much care for this game. I'll stick to a list of pros and cons.PROS:- Lord of the Rings theme.- Official soundtrack of the films.- A sense of humor, good for an occassional chuckle.- LAN multiplayer with up to 2 players, a rarity these days.CONS:- Fixed and unhelpful camera angles.- Quick Time Events as far as the eye can see.- Puzzles are extremely easy and generally only require you to press a button or two with the right character selected.- Poorly fitting dialogue and voices taken directly from the films and used regardless of tone of the scene in the game. Once Gimli even said one of Aragon's lines in Aragon's voice (""Mithril...!"").- Very confusing controls. Some menus require one set of keys while others require other keys. Only the movement keys are used for movement, the other 6 buttons seem to have been picked at random for every menu.- Singleplayer this game is very frustrating, as sometimes you must complete a number of mundanse tasks to continue. With two players this process can be sped up significantly. Fights with bosses (like a troll) are also much easier, since the troll will always be targetting a player.All in all a big disappointment."
