,Not Recommended,214510,33596950,Posted: 16 July,all,maelwys,"Having played through a number of the Lego games on various platforms, I found the Lord of the Rings LEGO game to be disappointing compared to others. The movie sequences are quite good - it has all the awesome signature moments from the movies that you want to see - but boss battles are repetitive affairs, the humor that is a hallmark of the games seems toned down and moments are few and far between, and the whole experience is marred by bugs and gameplay issues. More than once I had to restart a level simply because the game bugged and would not allow me to advance until I reloaded from a save. Add to this multiple pathing issues, jump puzzles that are pixel specific, and collectables that are nigh inaccessibile due to geometry and hit box bugs (ropes that characters fall through, balance areas that can't be jumped onto, etc), and it makes for a frustrating package that feels rushed and unfinished.TL;DR: If you want to experience the Lord of the Rings Trilogy, just go watch the films. It will take less time, and unless your DVD is scratched, you won't have to restart the scenes."
