76561198014263326,Recommended,214510,21556101,"Posted: 29 February, 2016",all,BoreusSimiusXXV,"LEGO The Lord of the Rings is in my opinion the best LEGO adaptation game. I'll admit I'm slightly biased as I'm obessed with Middle-Earth, but it s a perfectly balanced game. The LEGO series is well known by now for creating polished, solid, and extremely fun adaptations of existing franchises, and LEGO The Lord of the Rings is no exception.This game would have been fun enough if it had just followed the lead of LEGO Star Wars and simply the player a selection of levels based on the movies along with a small hub. However, LEGO LOTR not only provides this, it also includes a full open-world version of Middle-Earth to explore between each level. This open world isn't empty either, it's full of side-quests, collectables, and characters to unlock.As with pretty much every LEGO game, the gameplay is very casual, and not meant to be very challenging. This may put some people off, but most people know by now how LEGO games work. The gameplay is fun, the twists on the movies' memorable moments are hilarious, and collecting thousands of studs is still so addictive. If you are fan of either LEGO games or The Lord of the Rings, if you are just looking for a bit of casual fun, I couldn't recommend this game enough.9/10Often on sale so might be worth waiting, but it is certainly worth its full price anyway. Fantastic game."
