76561198041723757,Recommended,214510,4776413,"Posted: 16 July, 2013",all,ematan,"Taking the ring to the Mount Doom in Lego Style! A familiar story full of quirks and humor. The lego gameplay fits the LotR world surprisingly well.The ""hub"" is the best I've seen so far in any lego game. There are also loads of hidden things from the lore as well as a bunch of easter eggs. The cut scenes are directly from the movies - as well as any voice acting. This means that the game is even more loyal to the movie than some other lego games (HP, PotC, SW). This also makes the levels super linear and full of cut scenes (which you cannot skip on your first playthrough btw). This means that a level consists of a number of sequences and you cannot backtrack to a previous one without starting that level from the beginning.Unfortunately the game does not really add anything more to the mechanics either. It still is mostly smashing things to get coins, changing to a certain character to get stuff done and unlocking things in the attempt to get 100% complete.Still, I found the game addicting and do not regret the time spent with it. A person not familiar with LotR might not feel the same.TL:DRIf you love Middle Earth and silly stuff: Buy itIf you dislike grinding, too easy gameplay and have no interesting in LotR: Maybe not"
