76561198011484192,Recommended,214510,18804911,"Posted: 31 October, 2015",all,[SF] Jaydo,"This is a fun game, especially if you like Lego's but...1. Lego games are clearly made with Co-op in mind and this is no exception, so that means you need two controllers or a keyboard and a controller + a friend if you want the full experience, though you can still play alone alright.2. It is one of the buggier games out there. The bugs are not many but when they do show up they are somewhat game-breaking. For example, the Sauron fight at the very beginning is sometimes bugged to the point that you have to restart the game and you can't skip the long intro to that fight. The Xbox controller suddenly began to cut out every minute or so, killing your character unless you disconnect and reconnect it in time.3. The game is poorly ported from the consoles. You can quickly tell that you were not supposed to play this with the keyboard and there is no guarantee that it will support a non-xbox controller. Unless you already play games with a controller, you have to ask yourself if you are going to buy one just for this game?4. This is not a big problem, but you will quickly notice that the actors sound like someone with a cheap mic just recorded Lord of The Rings when it was on TV and put those recordings in the game.Some of the pro's are:- Co-op is well integrated into the gameplay for multiple players to feel useful.- Graphics and sound are...well they are Lego graphics and sound; they are fun if you are into that sort of thing- There are a lot of secrets, little puzzles and stuff to do. Pleasant level design overall.- Girls seem to like this game so you may get your partner to co-op"
